1. Download PHP from https://windows.php.net/download
2. Extract the Zip file
    2.1 Its not mandatory to extract the files should in Program files
        Because we the extracted copy will run the command php
3. Add path-to-extract-folder\php to the path environment variable
    To ensure Windows can find PHP, you need to change the path environment variable. Open Settings, type ‘environment variables’ 
    into the search field and open the result. Select the “Advanced” tab, and click the “Environment Variables” button. 
4. Restart your system
    Loading the set variable to os
